title: For Sale:  Remington Model 12A WW1, Trench Gun, Riot Gun, World War 1 12
postcontent: In good, decent condition, we have an extremely scarce rarely ever seen US WW1 issued Remington Model 10-A trench gun or possibly aerial training gun that was converted as nearly all of them were to riot gun configuration after the war in the very early post war period 1918-1921. It could have been a training gun because it was originally marked as modified choke. This could have been done by Remington or by the Army when converted. Only a few known example exist that remain in the Trench gun configuration and the most worn out example These shotguns were used by the Army and the Marines post WW1 and were also used by the Treasury Dept against Bootleggers and also the Post Office as well. According to Springfield Research an example made two guns before this one went to the US Post Office in 1921. This one stayed in Service probably through the end of WW2, although by that time they were worn out and withdrawn from service.

title: For Sale:  Century Arms Coach Gun
postcontent:
Up for sale today we have a cool little shotgun that could be very useful for a number of things, and won't break the bank to buy. This is a Century Arms JW-2000 12 Gauge Coach Gun with 20 inch barrels. This shotgun shoots 2 3/4 inch and 3 inch shells, and unlike most Coach Gun styles, which are cylinder bore, this one has chokes, making it much more useful for a wider variety of tasks. The right barrel is Modified Choke, and the left barrel is Full Choke. This means the gun will pattern better out to longer distances with shot loads. The gun has a decent blue finish, and a very nice looking wood stock. This is a solid gun and weighs in at about 8 pounds, so it won't beat you to death when you shoot it. It is very short and handy.
You can use this shotgun for home defense if you like. Its external hammers mean that it can safely be stored loaded, but un-cocked until needed, which you cannot do with an internal hammer gun. The chokes make it a great choice for a survival, camp, or hunting gun, in any role where you need a firearm but don't want to tie up a lot of money.
I've priced this gun so that it is easy to buy, but I will also listen to reasonable offers and consider trades. It never hurts to ask. You can see the gun by appointment at my office just outside of Homestead. All laws complied with. Thanks for looking at my listing.P.S. I listed this as a Stoeger, because that is the closest thing to the right brand. Century Arms is not a choice in the Armslist menu.
